## v1.2.0 (2026-05-09)

**Changed by:** ProjectOdyssey Phase G EASY-tier swarm consolidation (PR #5363)
**Verification:** verified-ci

### What changed

- Added Phase 10b "RESCUE — Consolidate Cross-Contaminated Worker PRs into One" — the
  cherry-pick consolidation recovery pattern when parallel dispatch on distinct branches
  has produced cross-contamination
- Added decision matrix: when to consolidate vs re-dispatch
- Added 1 Failed Attempts row: O(N^2) per-branch cleanup is worse than consolidation
- Added Verified On row for ProjectOdyssey #5363
- Added `history` frontmatter field (was missing in v1.1.0)
- Upgraded verification to `verified-ci`
- Bumped to 1.2.0 (minor — new phase, new failure, no breaking changes)
- Description trigger list extended to 7 conditions (added rescue pattern)

### Why

PR #5363 demonstrated that when parallel `Task isolation=worktree` dispatch on N distinct
branches produces cross-contaminated commits, attempting to salvage each branch
independently is O(N^2) — fixing one branch breaks another. Cherry-picking each worker's
intended commit into a single consolidated branch with multiple `Closes #N` lines is the
correct recovery path; close individual worker PRs with a reference comment.

---

## v1.1.0 (2026-05-06)

**Changed by:** HomericIntelligence/ProjectArgus Atlas v0.2.1 patch series (PRs #463-#474)
**Verification:** verified-local

### What changed
- Expanded `description` with two new triggers:
  - (5) launching >=2 concurrent sub-agents that each commit/push to the same git repo
  - (6) sub-agents report file bleed-over or unexpected `git checkout` reverts mid-task
- Added Phase 4 sub-section "Sub-Agent Brief Template (Wave Orchestration)" with the `/tmp/<repo-stem>-wt-<task>` per-agent path convention
- Added "Integration Base Branch Pattern" — single integration branch with `--base <integration-base>` per PR, single main merge at end
- Added "Trust-but-Verify Sub-Agent Reports" with the canonical `gh pr view --json mergeable,mergeStateStatus,state` verification call
- Added "Submodule Wrinkle" — `.git/modules/<submodule>` indirection in `git worktree list`
- Added "Per-PR Worktree Cleanup" — tear down per PR; never reuse a path across sub-agents
- Added 5 new Failed Attempts rows: shared-tree wave-1 collision, false auto-merge-armed report, skipped cleanup disk growth, briefs too short, reused worktree path
- Added "Do NOT use when" entries: single-agent short task, pure-research agents, agents needing cross-branch reads
- Added Verified On row for HomericIntelligence/ProjectArgus Atlas v0.2.1 (17 PRs, 6 waves)
- Bumped `verification` from `unverified` to `verified-local`
- Bumped version 1.0.0 -> 1.1.0
- Updated `date` to 2026-05-06

### Why
A multi-hour Atlas v0.2.1 patch series orchestrated ~17 PRs across 6 waves of parallel Opus sub-agents. Wave-1 used a shared working tree and immediately hit "working tree was twice reverted to the parent branch's state" bleed-over, forcing defensive `git reset --soft && commit` recovery. Switching to per-agent `/tmp/<repo-stem>-wt-<task>` worktrees fixed it cleanly — zero state interference across waves 2-6.

The session also surfaced two GitHub-API-truth lessons not previously captured here:
1. A sub-agent reported "auto-squash armed" but the PR was actually `mergeable: CONFLICTING` AND the repo forbids rebase merges (the original `--rebase` arming was a silent no-op). Verified via `gh pr view --json mergeable,mergeStateStatus`; switched to `--squash`.
2. Brief sizing matters: <50 lines and the agent guesses; >150 and it skims; ~80-120 lines is the sweet spot.

### Previous version (v1.0.0) snapshot

```yaml
name: parallel-pr-worktree-workflow
description: "Use when: (1) launching 2+ parallel rebase agents that need isolated git state to avoid branch collision, (2) implementing 5+ independent fixes in parallel PRs using git worktrees, (3) bulk-merging skill PRs with CI fixes and conflict resolution, (4) batching 10+ PRs across parallel sub-agents for maximum throughput."
category: ci-cd
date: 2026-03-28
version: "1.0.0"
verification: unverified
```
